This paper is about machine learning benchmarking, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper specifically discusses the challenges of benchmarking ML training and proposes a new benchmark called MLPerf. The paper also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), distributed computing (cs.DC), computer architecture (cs.AR), and computer vision (cs.CV), which are all potential sub-categories that could be relevant to this work.
